  "summary": "abi-encode ships base64-decoded payload executed at load time",
  "details": "The package's index.js contains multiple Buffer.from(..., 'base64') calls chained with.toString() decoding, consistent with an obfuscated payload assembled and executed when the module is required. Stage-1 tracing engaged with the file but its output was withheld by the provider content safety filter, a signal that the traced content matched malware-shaped patterns. The package name resembles a common Ethereum ABI utility, which is a plausible lure for typosquat installation.",
